"n.冒号 【英】 n.冒号(punctuation mark[:]) n. 冒号(用于引导一个引用语、解释说明、例子) 【记】把colon从上往下写, 在把两个o用笔图黑, 冒号就出现了. 【记】colon, 象形，有两个圆圈；colonel 校级军官；都至少是二星,也就是“:” colon (n.1)  punctuation mark, 1540s, from Latin colon ""part of a poem,"" from Greek kolon (with a long initial -o-) ""part of a verse,"" literally ""limb, member"" (especially the leg, but also of a tree limb), also, figuratively, ""a clause of a sentence,"" from PIE root *(s)kel- (3) ""bent, crooked"" (see scoliosis). Meaning evolved from ""independent clause"" to punctuation mark that sets it off. colon (n.2)  ""large intestine,"" late 14c., from Greek kolon (with a short initial -o-) ""large intestine,"" of unknown origin."
